OL,3,CWhat is the role of the King on
OL,4,Cresults day?
OL,6,FSunak has been told that he can,
OL,7,Fshould he wish, bring his wife and
OL,8,Fchildren to Buckingham Palace.
OL,10,FThey are met at the Sovereign's
OL,11,Fentrance by the King and Queen's
OL,12,FPrincipal Private Secretary, Sir Clive
OL,13,FAlderton, and one of the King's
OL,14,Fequerries.
OL,16,FThey will arrive in the quadrangle of
OL,17,Fthe palace and meet the Monarch in the
OL,18,Fprivate audience room, before Sunak
OL,19,Fdeparts by the back door (usually the
OL,20,Fgarden exit) to preserve some dignity.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
