OL,3,CWhat is the role of the King on
OL,4,Cresults day?
OL,6,FOnly the King and Starmer will be in
OL,7,Fthe audience room when the Monarch
OL,8,Fasks him to form a new administration.
OL,10,FThe Labour leader will not "kiss the
OL,11,Fhands" of the Monarch - as happened in
OL,12,Fthe past - but will instead bow.
OL,14,FTony Blair wrote in his memoirs that
OL,15,Fhe tripped on the carpet at this
OL,16,Fmoment and almost fell into the hands
OL,17,Fof Queen Elizabeth.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
