OL,3,CWhat is the role of the King on
OL,4,Cresults day?
OL,6,FHaving accepted the "commission" to
OL,7,Fform a new government, the King and
OL,8,Fhis new prime minister will have a
OL,9,Fbrief exchange.
OL,11,FIf he wants it, Starmer can have a
OL,12,Fmoment in another room to collect his
OL,13,Fthoughts and make final adjustments to
OL,14,Fhis big speech, before being shown out
OL,15,Fby an equerry.
OL,17,FThe prime minister will then be driven
OL,18,Fto Downing Street, where he will
OL,19,Faddress the nation outside the door of
OL,20,FNumber 10 at around 12.20pm.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
